Command.Name: AcquisitionStart
Command.ToolTip: Starts the acquisition of images.
Command.Description: Starts the acquisition of images. If the camera is configured for single frame acquisition, it will start the acquisition of one frame. If the camera is configured for continuous frame acquisition, it will start the continuous acquisition of frames.

Command.Name: AcquisitionStop
Command.ToolTip: Stops the acquisition of images.
Command.Description: Stops the acquisition of images if a continuous image acquisition is in progress.

Command.Name: AcquisitionAbort
Command.ToolTip: Aborts the acquisition of images.
Command.Description: Aborts the acquisition of images. If the camera is currently exposing a frame, the camera stops exposing immediately. The readout process, if already started, is aborted. The current frame will be incomplete. Afterwards, image acquisition is switched off.

Command.Name: BslSensorStandby

Command.Description: Puts the sensor in standby mode. In standby mode, power consumption is reduced significantly, which results in a lower camera temperature. Certain parameters can only be configured when the sensor is in standby mode.

Command.Name: BslSensorOn
Command.ToolTip: Switches the sensor power on.
Command.Description: Switches the sensor power on.

Enumeration.Name: GainAuto

Enumeration.Description: Sets the operation mode of the Gain Auto auto function. The Gain Auto auto function automatically adjusts the gain within set limits until a target brightness value has been reached.

EnumEntry.Name: Off
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Automatic gain adjustment is disabled.
EnumEntry.Description: Automatic gain adjustment is disabled.

EnumEntry.Name: Once
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The gain is adjusted automatically to reach the specifed target value.
EnumEntry.Description: The gain is adjusted automatically to reach the specifed target value. When the target value has been reached, the auto function will automatically be set to Off and the new parameter value will be applied to the following images.

EnumEntry.Name: Continuous
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The gain is adjusted continuously while images are being acquired.
EnumEntry.Description: The gain is adjusted continuously while images are being acquired. The adjustment process will continue until the parameter is set to Once or Off.
